text:
you can just write your own code for a form element i.e.: ```&lt;form action="https://forms.HubSpot.com/uploads/form/v2/HUBID/FORM-GUID" method="POST"&gt;
		&lt;input type="text" name="firstname"&gt;
		&lt;input type="text" name="lastname"&gt;
		&lt;input type="email" name="email"&gt;
		&lt;input type="submit" value="Continue"&gt;
	&lt;/form&gt;```
As long as the input type and name match those in the form you've created in HubSpot, the form will submit fine as "Submitted through API on page: Not included in API data"

this is what that existing code looks like:
```
&lt;!--[if lte IE 8]&gt;
&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/v2-legacy.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;![endif]--&gt;
&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;// &lt;![CDATA[
hbspt.forms.create({
	portalId: "2418268",
	formId: "85bb1452-86ac-4d1e-bfb4-f158f026a0f1",
	css: '',
	cssClass: 'scholarship-form',
	onFormSubmit: function(data){
	    if((data[0][3].value !== "") &amp;&amp; (data[0][2].value !== "")){
    	    if((data[0][3].value === "Graduate" || data[0][3].value === "Undergraduate") &amp;&amp; (data[0][2].value === "Excellent (over 720)" || data[0][2].value === "Good (691 to 719)" || data[0][2].value === "Ok (651 to 690)")) {
                window.location = "https://www.cometfi.com/redirect/lendkey100";
            } else {
                window.location = "https://www.cometfi.com/refi-ready-b";
            }
	    }
	} 
});
// ]]&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
```
